{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":530,"text":"So let's start with some good news,"},{"time":3491,"text":"and the good news has to do with what do we know"},{"time":5840,"text":"based on biomedical research"},{"time":8107,"text":"that actually has changed the outcomes"},{"time":11561,"text":"for many very serious diseases?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":14660,"text":"Let's start with leukemia,"},{"time":16907,"text":"acute lymphoblastic leukemia, ALL,"},{"time":19435,"text":"the most common cancer of children."},{"time":21873,"text":"When I was a student,"},{"time":23835,"text":"the mortality rate was about 95 percent."},{"time":27675,"text":"Today, some 25, 30 years later, we're talking about"},{"time":30808,"text":"a mortality rate that's reduced by 85 percent."},{"time":34435,"text":"Six thousand children each year"},{"time":37051,"text":"who would have previously died of this disease are cured."},{"time":41240,"text":"If you want the really big numbers,"},{"time":43031,"text":"look at these numbers for heart disease."},{"time":45859,"text":"Heart disease used to be the biggest killer,"},{"time":47651,"text":"particularly for men in their 40s."},{"time":49155,"text":"Today, we've seen a 63-percent reduction in mortality"},{"time":52649,"text":"from heart disease --"},{"time":54710,"text":"remarkably, 1.1 million deaths averted every year."},{"time":59595,"text":"AIDS, incredibly, has just been named,"},{"time":62316,"text":"in the past month, a chronic disease,"},{"time":64597,"text":"meaning that a 20-year-old who becomes infected with HIV"},{"time":67512,"text":"is expected not to live weeks, months, or a couple of years,"},{"time":71583,"text":"as we said only a decade ago,"},{"time":73853,"text":"but is thought to live decades,"},{"time":76245,"text":"probably to die in his '60s or '70s from other causes altogether."},{"time":80741,"text":"These are just remarkable, remarkable changes"},{"time":83766,"text":"in the outlook for some of the biggest killers."},{"time":86355,"text":"And one in particular"},{"time":88434,"text":"that you probably wouldn't know about, stroke,"},{"time":90479,"text":"which has been, along with heart disease,"},{"time":92080,"text":"one of the biggest killers in this country,"},{"time":94258,"text":"is a disease in which now we know"},{"time":96049,"text":"that if you can get people into the emergency room"},{"time":98978,"text":"within three hours of the onset,"},{"time":101152,"text":"some 30 percent of them will be able to leave the hospital"},{"time":103757,"text":"without any disability whatsoever."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106876,"text":"Remarkable stories,"},{"time":109133,"text":"good-news stories,"},{"time":111164,"text":"all of which boil down to understanding"},{"time":114229,"text":"something about the diseases that has allowed us"},{"time":117581,"text":"to detect early and intervene early."},{"time":120904,"text":"Early detection, early intervention,"},{"time":123039,"text":"that's the story for these successes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126109,"text":"Unfortunately, the news is not all good."},{"time":128845,"text":"Let's talk about one other story"},{"time":131194,"text":"which has to do with suicide."},{"time":132885,"text":"Now this is, of course, not a disease, per se."},{"time":135537,"text":"It's a condition, or it's a situation"},{"time":138625,"text":"that leads to mortality."},{"time":140414,"text":"What you may not realize is just how prevalent it is."},{"time":143494,"text":"There are 38,000 suicides each year in the United States."},{"time":147703,"text":"That means one about every 15 minutes."},{"time":150461,"text":"Third most common cause of death amongst people"},{"time":153237,"text":"between the ages of 15 and 25."},{"time":156013,"text":"It's kind of an extraordinary story when you realize"},{"time":158261,"text":"that this is twice as common as homicide"},{"time":160773,"text":"and actually more common as a source of death"},{"time":163422,"text":"than traffic fatalities in this country."},{"time":166757,"text":"Now, when we talk about suicide,"},{"time":169389,"text":"there is also a medical contribution here,"},{"time":172501,"text":"because 90 percent of suicides"},{"time":174933,"text":"are related to a mental illness:"},{"time":176703,"text":"depression, bipolar disorder, schizophrenia,"},{"time":179749,"text":"anorexia, borderline personality. There's a long list"},{"time":182808,"text":"of disorders that contribute,"},{"time":184917,"text":"and as I mentioned before, often early in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188941,"text":"But it's not just the mortality from these disorders."},{"time":192145,"text":"It's also morbidity."},{"time":193787,"text":"If you look at disability,"},{"time":196048,"text":"as measured by the World Health Organization"},{"time":198200,"text":"with something they call the Disability Adjusted Life Years,"},{"time":201725,"text":"it's kind of a metric that nobody would think of"},{"time":203821,"text":"except an economist,"},{"time":205135,"text":"except it's one way of trying to capture what is lost"},{"time":208577,"text":"in terms of disability from medical causes,"},{"time":211760,"text":"and as you can see, virtually 30 percent"},{"time":214653,"text":"of all disability from all medical causes"},{"time":216917,"text":"can be attributed to mental disorders,"},{"time":219477,"text":"neuropsychiatric syndromes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221861,"text":"You're probably thinking that doesn't make any sense."},{"time":224013,"text":"I mean, cancer seems far more serious."},{"time":226685,"text":"Heart disease seems far more serious."},{"time":229717,"text":"But you can see actually they are further down this list,"},{"time":232757,"text":"and that's because we're talking here about disability."},{"time":235037,"text":"What drives the disability for these disorders"},{"time":237829,"text":"like schizophrenia and bipolar and depression?"},{"time":241733,"text":"Why are they number one here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":244708,"text":"Well, there are probably three reasons."},{"time":246217,"text":"One is that they're highly prevalent."},{"time":248189,"text":"About one in five people will suffer from one of these disorders"},{"time":251484,"text":"in the course of their lifetime."},{"time":254061,"text":"A second, of course, is that, for some people,"},{"time":256381,"text":"these become truly disabling,"},{"time":257965,"text":"and it's about four to five percent, perhaps one in 20."},{"time":261093,"text":"But what really drives these numbers, this high morbidity,"},{"time":265357,"text":"and to some extent the high mortality,"},{"time":267786,"text":"is the fact that these start very early in life."},{"time":271734,"text":"Fifty percent will have onset by age 14,"},{"time":274829,"text":"75 percent by age 24,"},{"time":277949,"text":"a picture that is very different than what one would see"},{"time":281414,"text":"if you're talking about cancer or heart disease,"},{"time":283685,"text":"diabetes, hypertension -- most of the major illnesses"},{"time":287085,"text":"that we think about as being sources of morbidity and mortality."},{"time":291181,"text":"These are, indeed, the chronic disorders of young people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297491,"text":"Now, I started by telling you that there were some good-news stories."},{"time":300358,"text":"This is obviously not one of them."},{"time":301806,"text":"This is the part of it that is perhaps most difficult,"},{"time":304685,"text":"and in a sense this is a kind of confession for me."},{"time":307269,"text":"My job is to actually make sure that we make progress"},{"time":312621,"text":"on all of these disorders."},{"time":314973,"text":"I work for the federal government."},{"time":316683,"text":"Actually, I work for you. You pay my salary."},{"time":318701,"text":"And maybe at this point, when you know what I do,"},{"time":321085,"text":"or maybe what I've failed to do,"},{"time":323205,"text":"you'll think that I probably ought to be fired,"},{"time":325414,"text":"and I could certainly understand that."},{"time":327569,"text":"But what I want to suggest, and the reason I'm here"},{"time":329901,"text":"is to tell you that I think we're about to be"},{"time":333156,"text":"in a very different world as we think about these illnesses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337819,"text":"What I've been talking to you about so far is mental disorders,"},{"time":340925,"text":"diseases of the mind."},{"time":342641,"text":"That's actually becoming a rather unpopular term these days,"},{"time":346037,"text":"and people feel that, for whatever reason,"},{"time":348237,"text":"it's politically better to use the term behavioral disorders"},{"time":351614,"text":"and to talk about these as disorders of behavior."},{"time":355525,"text":"Fair enough. They are disorders of behavior,"},{"time":357792,"text":"and they are disorders of the mind."},{"time":359792,"text":"But what I want to suggest to you"},{"time":362197,"text":"is that both of those terms,"},{"time":363949,"text":"which have been in play for a century or more,"},{"time":366967,"text":"are actually now impediments to progress,"},{"time":369787,"text":"that what we need conceptually to make progress here"},{"time":374117,"text":"is to rethink these disorders as brain disorders."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379325,"text":"Now, for some of you, you're going to say,"},{"time":381187,"text":"\"Oh my goodness, here we go again."},{"time":383406,"text":"We're going to hear about a biochemical imbalance"},{"time":386034,"text":"or we're going to hear about drugs"},{"time":387769,"text":"or we're going to hear about some very simplistic notion"},{"time":392595,"text":"that will take our subjective experience"},{"time":395535,"text":"and turn it into molecules, or maybe into some sort of"},{"time":401607,"text":"very flat, unidimensional understanding"},{"time":404825,"text":"of what it is to have depression or schizophrenia."}]},{"cues":[{"time":408927,"text":"When we talk about the brain, it is anything but"},{"time":413425,"text":"unidimensional or simplistic or reductionistic."},{"time":416688,"text":"It depends, of course, on what scale"},{"time":419647,"text":"or what scope you want to think about,"},{"time":421943,"text":"but this is an organ of surreal complexity,"},{"time":428223,"text":"and we are just beginning to understand"},{"time":431694,"text":"how to even study it, whether you're thinking about"},{"time":433867,"text":"the 100 billion neurons that are in the cortex"},{"time":436449,"text":"or the 100 trillion synapses"},{"time":438594,"text":"that make up all the connections."},{"time":440953,"text":"We have just begun to try to figure out"},{"time":444529,"text":"how do we take this very complex machine"},{"time":448057,"text":"that does extraordinary kinds of information processing"},{"time":450801,"text":"and use our own minds to understand"},{"time":453518,"text":"this very complex brain that supports our own minds."},{"time":457049,"text":"It's actually a kind of cruel trick of evolution"},{"time":459609,"text":"that we simply don't have a brain"},{"time":463439,"text":"that seems to be wired well enough to understand itself."},{"time":466337,"text":"In a sense, it actually makes you feel that"},{"time":468651,"text":"when you're in the safe zone of studying behavior or cognition,"},{"time":471489,"text":"something you can observe,"},{"time":472812,"text":"that in a way feels more simplistic and reductionistic"},{"time":475817,"text":"than trying to engage this very complex, mysterious organ"},{"time":480785,"text":"that we're beginning to try to understand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483213,"text":"Now, already in the case of the brain disorders"},{"time":486869,"text":"that I've been talking to you about,"},{"time":488597,"text":"depression, obsessive compulsive disorder,"},{"time":490870,"text":"post-traumatic stress disorder,"},{"time":493032,"text":"while we don't have an in-depth understanding"},{"time":495974,"text":"of how they are abnormally processed"},{"time":499700,"text":"or what the brain is doing in these illnesses,"},{"time":501805,"text":"we have been able to already identify"},{"time":504860,"text":"some of the connectional differences, or some of the ways"},{"time":507436,"text":"in which the circuitry is different"},{"time":509940,"text":"for people who have these disorders."},{"time":511756,"text":"We call this the human connectome,"},{"time":513514,"text":"and you can think about the connectome"},{"time":515895,"text":"sort of as the wiring diagram of the brain."},{"time":517767,"text":"You'll hear more about this in a few minutes."},{"time":519871,"text":"The important piece here is that as you begin to look"},{"time":522822,"text":"at people who have these disorders, the one in five of us"},{"time":526799,"text":"who struggle in some way,"},{"time":528627,"text":"you find that there's a lot of variation"},{"time":530915,"text":"in the way that the brain is wired,"},{"time":534131,"text":"but there are some predictable patterns, and those patterns"},{"time":536733,"text":"are risk factors for developing one of these disorders."},{"time":540547,"text":"It's a little different than the way we think about brain disorders"},{"time":543539,"text":"like Huntington's or Parkinson's or Alzheimer's disease"},{"time":546307,"text":"where you have a bombed-out part of your cortex."},{"time":548699,"text":"Here we're talking about traffic jams, or sometimes detours,"},{"time":551959,"text":"or sometimes problems with just the way that things are connected"},{"time":554706,"text":"and the way that the brain functions."},{"time":555953,"text":"You could, if you want, compare this to,"},{"time":559123,"text":"on the one hand, a myocardial infarction, a heart attack,"},{"time":562172,"text":"where you have dead tissue in the heart,"},{"time":563995,"text":"versus an arrhythmia, where the organ simply isn't functioning"},{"time":567592,"text":"because of the communication problems within it."},{"time":569843,"text":"Either one would kill you; in only one of them"},{"time":571812,"text":"will you find a major lesion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574412,"text":"As we think about this, probably it's better to actually go"},{"time":577244,"text":"a little deeper into one particular disorder, and that would be schizophrenia,"},{"time":580467,"text":"because I think that's a good case"},{"time":582603,"text":"for helping to understand why thinking of this as a brain disorder matters."},{"time":586128,"text":"These are scans from Judy Rapoport and her colleagues"},{"time":590006,"text":"at the National Institute of Mental Health"},{"time":592178,"text":"in which they studied children with very early onset schizophrenia,"},{"time":595894,"text":"and you can see already in the top"},{"time":597364,"text":"there's areas that are red or orange, yellow,"},{"time":599901,"text":"are places where there's less gray matter,"},{"time":602039,"text":"and as they followed them over five years,"},{"time":603577,"text":"comparing them to age match controls,"},{"time":605815,"text":"you can see that, particularly in areas like"},{"time":607637,"text":"the dorsolateral prefrontal cortex"},{"time":609953,"text":"or the superior temporal gyrus, there's a profound loss of gray matter."},{"time":614283,"text":"And it's important, if you try to model this,"},{"time":615826,"text":"you can think about normal development"},{"time":617782,"text":"as a loss of cortical mass, loss of cortical gray matter,"},{"time":621035,"text":"and what's happening in schizophrenia is that you overshoot that mark,"},{"time":624699,"text":"and at some point, when you overshoot,"},{"time":626268,"text":"you cross a threshold, and it's that threshold"},{"time":629259,"text":"where we say, this is a person who has this disease,"},{"time":632835,"text":"because they have the behavioral symptoms"},{"time":635123,"text":"of hallucinations and delusions."},{"time":637244,"text":"That's something we can observe."},{"time":638721,"text":"But look at this closely and you can see that actually they've crossed a different threshold."},{"time":644363,"text":"They've crossed a brain threshold much earlier,"},{"time":647359,"text":"that perhaps not at age 22 or 20,"},{"time":650499,"text":"but even by age 15 or 16 you can begin to see"},{"time":653267,"text":"the trajectory for development is quite different"},{"time":655627,"text":"at the level of the brain, not at the level of behavior."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659142,"text":"Why does this matter? Well first because,"},{"time":661237,"text":"for brain disorders, behavior is the last thing to change."},{"time":664379,"text":"We know that for Alzheimer's, for Parkinson's, for Huntington's."},{"time":667289,"text":"There are changes in the brain a decade or more"},{"time":669723,"text":"before you see the first signs of a behavioral change."},{"time":674763,"text":"The tools that we have now allow us to detect"},{"time":677707,"text":"these brain changes much earlier, long before the symptoms emerge."},{"time":682004,"text":"But most important, go back to where we started."},{"time":685403,"text":"The good-news stories in medicine"},{"time":688619,"text":"are early detection, early intervention."},{"time":691563,"text":"If we waited until the heart attack,"},{"time":695227,"text":"we would be sacrificing 1.1 million lives"},{"time":699202,"text":"every year in this country to heart disease."},{"time":701611,"text":"That is precisely what we do today"},{"time":704019,"text":"when we decide that everybody with one of these brain disorders,"},{"time":708531,"text":"brain circuit disorders, has a behavioral disorder."},{"time":711733,"text":"We wait until the behavior becomes manifest."},{"time":714957,"text":"That's not early detection. That's not early intervention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719516,"text":"Now to be clear, we're not quite ready to do this."},{"time":721321,"text":"We don't have all the facts. We don't actually even know"},{"time":724475,"text":"what the tools will be,"},{"time":727024,"text":"nor what to precisely look for in every case to be able"},{"time":731283,"text":"to get there before the behavior emerges as different."},{"time":735488,"text":"But this tells us how we need to think about it,"},{"time":738425,"text":"and where we need to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":739914,"text":"Are we going to be there soon?"},{"time":741116,"text":"I think that this is something that will happen"},{"time":743794,"text":"over the course of the next few years, but I'd like to finish"},{"time":746625,"text":"with a quote about trying to predict how this will happen"},{"time":749160,"text":"by somebody who's thought a lot about changes"},{"time":751521,"text":"in concepts and changes in technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":753849,"text":"\"We always overestimate the change that will occur"},{"time":756113,"text":"in the next two years and underestimate"},{"time":758336,"text":"the change that will occur in the next 10.\" -- Bill Gates."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762212,"text":"Thanks very much."},{"time":763575,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}